The similarity ratio is fundamental to the accurate execution of laboratory-scale tunnel model tests. By appropriately scaling the physical and mechanical properties of materials from actual tunnel projects, the similarity ratio ensures that experimental results reliably reflect real tunnel behavior30. Considering the cross-sectional dimensions of the Xinmajie Tunnel and the laboratory conditions, based on the similarity principle, the similarity constant Cγ = 1, and the geometric similarity constant Cl = 40 between the similar stratum and the original stratum are determined. These two ratios served as the fundamental similarity bases for the model design (Eq. 1). Based on these criteria, the remaining physical and mechanical parameters of the model materials were derived accordingly, as summarized in Table 1.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
