Gypsum is widely recognized as an ideal elastic material, and is commonly used for lining fabrication in tunnel model experiments33. Therefore, gypsum is selected as the main material of lining in this paper. Considering the large discreteness of gypsum, the density should not be used as the main control parameter, so the elastic modulus and compressive strength are used as the control index of the material25. The primary support of the Xinmajie Tunnel construction adopts C25 shotcrete with a thickness of 25 cm. To facilitate the production of the lining model, the steel arch is simplified according to the principle of stiffness equivalence, see Eq. (2)33–35. By calculation, the primary and secondary linings were represented by equivalent thicknesses of 30 cm and 60 cm of C30 concrete, respectively. The mechanical parameters of similar lining materials were obtained by universal testing machine, and the material ratio was adjusted according to the results. The final optimized mix ratio was determined to be water: gypsum = 1: 0.7, with the corresponding mechanical parameters summarized in Table 3. Notably, due to the inherently low tensile strength of gypsum, which makes it prone to cracking, double layers of steel mesh were embedded during the casting process to enhance its tensile resistance and ensure smooth demolding after curing (Fig. 4).2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
